					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/joe-raveneye" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3684647); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3684647&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183022" alt="Joe Raveneye" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3684647)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/joe-raveneye" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3684647); return false;" >Joe Raveneye</a></span> <span class="odate time_1519165676 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Feb 2018 22:27</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3716931">
									

<p>The problem with being God is that the moment you fix all the problems, everybody knows something is fishy. Take a look at what happens when Jim Carey decides that everybody who prays to him wins the lottery. In this reality, fixing all the problems instantly will put the entire Foundation out of business, which negates the necessity of this reality's existence.</p>
<p>Assuming 2317 exists in the same reality as this 001, it would be far more prudent to let the Foundation continue to try to contain 2317, and only neutralize it for them the moment the last chain snaps.</p>

							</div>

								
					
